-103; Howe, G.T., Saruul, P., Davis, J., Chen, T.H.H., Quantitative genetics of bud phenology, frost damage and winter survival in an F2 family of hybrid poplar (2000) Theoretical & Applied Genetics, 101, pp. 632-642; Ibáñez, C., Kozarewa, I., Johansson, M., Ögren, E., Rohde, A., Eriksson, M.E., Circadian clock components regulate entry and affect exit of seasonal dormancy as well as winter hardiness in Populus trees (2010) Plant Physiology, 153, pp. 1823-1833; Imbert, E., Lefèvre, F., Dispersal and gene flow of Populus nigra (Salicaceae) along a dynamic river system (2003) Journal of Ecology, 91, pp. 447-456; Ingvarsson, P.K., García, M.V., Hall, D., Luquez, V., Jansson, S., Clinal variation in phyB2, a candidate gene for day-length-induced growth cessation and bud set, across a latitudinal gradient in European aspen (Populus tremula) (2006) Genetics, 172, pp. 1845-1853; Ingvarsson, P.K., Garcia, M.V., Luquez, V., Hall, D., Jansson, S., Nucleotide polymorphism and phenotypic associations within and around the phytochrome B2 locus in European aspen (Populus tremula, Salicaceae) (2008) Genetics, 178, pp. 2217-2226; Jiménez, S., Lawton-Rauh, A.L., Reighard, G.L., Abbott, A.G., Bielenberg, D.G., Phylogenetic analysis and molecular evolution of the dormancy associated MADS-box genes from peach (2009) BMC Plant Biology, 9, p. 81; Jorge, V., Dowkiw, A., Faivre-Rampant, P., Bastien, C., Genetic architecture of qualitative and quantitative Melampsora larici-populina leaf rust resistance in hybrid poplar: genetic mapping and QTL detection (2005) New Phytologist, 167, pp. 113-127; Junttila, O., The cessation of apical growth in latitudinal ecotypes and ecotype crosses of Salix pentandra L (1982) Journal of Experimental Botany, 33, pp. 1021-1029; Junttila, O., Nilsen, J., Igeland, B., Effect of temperature on the induction of bud dormancy in ecotypes of Betula pubescens and Betula pendula (2003) Scandinavian Journal of Forestry Research, 18, pp. 208-217; Kvaalen, H., Johnsen Ø